      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ksu-cs-textbooks.github.io/cc210/11-file-system/01-file-everything/</guid>
      <description>Modern computer systems contain advanced file systems that allow us to store and retrieve vast amounts of data at ease. We&amp;rsquo;ve come a long way from the tape-drives and gigantic storage devices of years past. Now even the smallest computers can store tens if not hundreds of gigabytes of data on devices smaller than a fingernail.
1
Computers store data internally on physical devices such as the hard disk drive shown above, as well as solid state drives such as flash drives and SD cards that we&amp;rsquo;re familiar with today.</description>
