    <item>
      <title>Things to Keep in Mind</title>
      <link>https://ksu-cs-textbooks.github.io/cc210/11-file-system/05-things-to-mind/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ksu-cs-textbooks.github.io/cc210/11-file-system/05-things-to-mind/</guid>
      <description>Operating System and File Access Linux systems connect programs to the files by use of file descriptors. Linux must keep track of and de-conflict access to all file descriptors used by all processes at all times. There are a lot of processes in a modern computer, as I am typing this section, my Windows 10 machine has 5-applications and 92-background programs&amp;ndash;each of which may be accessing 0 or more file descriptors.</description>
    </item>
