      <description>Working with files is a very important feature of most computer programs. It can be tedious to manually enter data into a program, and likewise it is very helpful to be able to save the output for use later.
There are many more advanced things that we can do with files. For example, in a later module we’ll see how to build our own objects in code, and then save those objects to a file so we can use them again later.</description>
